<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Circumtropical. Within the study region recorded from China* (Yunnan), India (Tamil Nadu, West Bengal), Laos, Myanmar, Taiwan, Thailand, Vietnam. Introduced to Europe (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.56.529" author="Kirkendall, LR" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="227 - 251" refId="B232" refString="Kirkendall, LR, Faccoli, M, 2010. Bark beetles and pinhole borers (Curculionidae, Scolytinae, Platypodinae) alien to Europe. ZooKeys 56: 227 - 251, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.56.529" title="Bark beetles and pinhole borers (Curculionidae, Scolytinae, Platypodinae) alien to Europe." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.56.529" volume="56" year="2010">Kirkendall and Faccoli 2010</bibRefCitation>
) and South and Central America (
<bibRefCitation author="Wood, SL" journalOrPublisher="Great Basin Naturalist Memoirs" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 1359" refId="B483" refString="Wood, SL, 1982. The bark and ambrosia beetles of North and Central America (Coleoptera: Scolytidae), a taxonomic monograph. Great Basin Naturalist Memoirs 8: 1 - 1359" title="The bark and ambrosia beetles of North and Central America (Coleoptera: Scolytidae), a taxonomic monograph." volume="8" year="1982">Wood 1982</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Wood, SL" journalOrPublisher="Bean Life Science Museum, Provo" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B489" refString="Wood, SL, 2007. Bark and Ambrosia Beetles of South America (Coleoptera: Scolytidae). Brigham Young University, M.L. Bean Life Science Museum, Provo" title="Bark and Ambrosia Beetles of South America (Coleoptera: Scolytidae). Brigham Young University, M. L." year="2007">2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
