<bibRefCitation author="Dole, SA" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the California of Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="451 - 545" refId="B109" refString="Dole, SA, Cognato, AI, 2010. Revision of Xylosandrus Reitter (Curculionidae: Scolytinae). Proceedings of the California of Science 61: 451 - 545" title="Revision of Xylosandrus Reitter (Curculionidae: Scolytinae)." volume="61" year="2010">Dole and Cognato 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The biology has been studied by 
<bibRefCitation author="Browne, FG" journalOrPublisher="Sarawak Museum Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="300 - 318" refId="B69" refString="Browne, FG, 1961a. Borer beetles from Bako National Park (Sarawak). Sarawak Museum Journal 10: 300 - 318" title="Borer beetles from Bako National Park (Sarawak)." volume="10" year="1961 a">Browne (1961a)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Kalshoven, LGE" journalOrPublisher="Tijdschrift voor Entomologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="93 - 110" refId="B222" refString="Kalshoven, LGE, 1961. A study of the twig borer Xyleborus morigerus Blandford, mainly based on observations in Java. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie 104: 93 - 110" title="A study of the twig borer Xyleborus morigerus Blandford, mainly based on observations in Java." volume="104" year="1961">Kalshoven (1961)</bibRefCitation>
. These and other studies are reviewed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schedl, KE" journalOrPublisher="Revista de Entomologia de Mocambique" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 594" refId="B399" refString="Schedl, KE, 1963a. Scolytidae und Platypodidae Afrikas. Band II. Familie Scolytidae (Fortsetzung), Unterfamilie Ipinae (Fortsetzung). Revista de Entomologia de Mocambique 5: 1 - 594" title="Scolytidae und Platypodidae Afrikas. Band II. Familie Scolytidae (Fortsetzung), Unterfamilie Ipinae (Fortsetzung)." volume="5" year="1963 a">Schedl (1963a)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Le Pelley, RH" journalOrPublisher="Ltd., London and Harlow" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B243" refString="Le Pelley, RH, 1968. Pests of Coffee. Longmans, Green and Co. Ltd., London and Harlow" title="Pests of Coffee. Longmans, Green and Co." year="1968">Le Pelley (1968)</bibRefCitation>
. The species has some economic importance as a pest of coffee (
<bibRefCitation author="Kalshoven, LGE" journalOrPublisher="Tijdschrift voor Entomologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="93 - 110" refId="B222" refString="Kalshoven, LGE, 1961. A study of the twig borer Xyleborus morigerus Blandford, mainly based on observations in Java. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie 104: 93 - 110" title="A study of the twig borer Xyleborus morigerus Blandford, mainly based on observations in Java." volume="104" year="1961">Kalshoven 1961</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Le Pelley, RH" journalOrPublisher="Ltd., London and Harlow" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B243" refString="Le Pelley, RH, 1968. Pests of Coffee. Longmans, Green and Co. Ltd., London and Harlow" title="Pests of Coffee. Longmans, Green and Co." year="1968">Le Pelley 1968</bibRefCitation>
) and of other crop trees.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
